description: This stunning big Healey 3000 has been with the same owner for over 40 years.The car had a complete documented restoration in 1997.The last owner had over 25 British cars in his collection,this was his baby that was used on a regular basis.There are restorations and there are restorations,this man knew how to sort cars and did well sorting this car during restoration.Everything works as it was designed  and does it well.From the Overdrive unit to the operation of the door handles as well as the fit of the doors,the car simply comes together.The Austin Healey car was the marque that got me started in the collector car business in the 70's,decades later I am still in love with the marque.Every example that comes through our doors either as a derelict or a restored example,I want to keep,this is no exception.What a treat to drive a 3000 when they are sorted and all work as it should.I have posted over 80 pictures of this car with no photoshop,just as I see the car.Review the pictures,note how straight and true the car comes together,the aluminum cowl is razor straight,the body gaps are a perfect factory fit.Review the undercarriage and note the lack of corrosion(the car was a Texas,Alabama car).The interior and mechanics are as nice and strong as the car is beautiful.The gauges work perfectly.The car runs cool and smooth even on these hot summer days.The overdrive works without hesitation.The glass and chrome are without flaw.
The car is located at our indoor facility 25 miles east of downtown Nashville Tn.Independent inspections are welcomed and encouraged.
There will be an additional $299 for dealer doc fees on the final transaction price.

Sunnyside Chevrolet of Elyria, Ohio in conjunction with Greg's Sports, Classic, & Muscle is proud to offer for sale this 1965 Big Healey BJ8 Phase 2.Get out your leather driving helmet and goggles....Always one of John and Greg's favorites because they have been British car guys for over 30 years this Big Healey is the epitome of the peak of the British Sports Car Market. She's a 1965 BJ8 Phase 2 and I know some of you experts out there are wondering where the dual marker lights are- well do your homework and you'll find the early phase two cars had single marker lights and this is one of those cars. Us Pawluk's speak Healey.We bought this magnificent car because of the quality of the restoration. Starting with a very rust-free example this originally white car has been Ground Up, Frame Off, whatever you want to call it restored. Every nut and bolt has been touched and renewed, and the bottom of the car is just as pretty as the top. While notorious for rust issues this Healey came from Alabama and had such limited rust cut out of it we have the original metal and its extremely minor perhaps amounting to a total of a couple of sheets of paper worth in size- Amazing.Finished in correct Healey Red over Black coves this car is immaculate in fit and finish. The fit and finish is long past whatever the Healey Company was capable of back in the day. Leather interior, wood dash, new carpets- its all done and truly beautiful. Open the bonnet and you will see amazing quality work. Again, every nut and bolt has been turned, restored or refreshed. The BJ8 is arguably one of the top two or three dogs in Austin Healey collecting and long thought to be their best driving mannered and useable car.Not sure what else to say about this car if you know Healeys and have a good understanding of what it takes to get one to this level you know the value represented here.Drive it, show it, keep it in a bubble and polish it as a prized possession, the choice is yours once you make it yours.We stand behind our thoughts on this car by offering our travel expenses guarantee- come see the car and if we have materially misrepresented its condition we will gladly pay half of your travel expenses up to $500.00- this offer had been in place since we sold our first classic and we haven't paid the money yet.... We pride ourselves on having good cars and representing them properly.Additional pictures and video are available, please call 440-365-7311 for more photos, information or to schedule a test drive.

On offer here is rare tri-carb Austin Healey 3000. This car has been fully restored and includes some interesting and desirable upgrades. One is a modern five speed transmission providing synchromesh in all forward gears, better gear spacing, and overdrive fifth (and it dosen't leak).  Another is its aluminum wheels which are true knock-off type wheels, not bolt on types.  It also has a stainless steel exhaust system.  This car was under the stewardship of a single owner going back over 30 years.  That owner acquired the car as what he describes as a basket case.  Under his care it was body off frame restored and the body, frame, and undercarriage are all solid and rust free.  The paint presents very well without noticeable flaws.   Its attractive interior is finished in red leather with white piping is excellent throughout. The carpets are in fine condition with no indication of wear.  The engine was rebuilt and hardened valve seats installed in the head for compatibility with lead free fuel.  It has a Pertronix ignition and was upgraded to a modern alternator.  The engine is in top condition, holding excellent oil pressure, no exhaust smoke, and delivers strong performance.  The five speed is a Toyota Supra unit and one of the Smitty conversions which can be read about on various Internet and Healey sites.  The clutch action is smooth and the modern five speed transmission adds to the driving experience without the maintenance worries that accompanied the original gearboxes in these cars.  The brakes, suspension, and steering are all in good order.  This car needs nothing other than a new caretaker to drive and enjoy the Big Healey experience. This English beauty is a 1960 Austin-Healey 3000. The unmistakeable lines of this classic roadster are unmatched by today's cars. This particular Healey is a very desireable bright red exterior and black interior. It is a 2+2 roadster, with a tonneau cover that can be removed completely, half zipped for just driver access, or covered completely for storage.

There isn't a more perfect good weather vehicle than a classic British roadster. With the four speed shifter in your hand and the wind in your hair, the world's roads are your playground. This car is completely restored to original condition.

The inline 6 cylinder engine provides great power and torque, and a nice throaty growl under throttle. Have a seat in it once and you'll be hooked. Stop by today to start the summer off right with this classic open air dream car.

Built from 1959 through 1967 the 3000 transitioned from open sports car to a child-transporting 2 plus 2 option to a sports convertible.  The 3- liter was a highly successful car, not only in the sales arena but also racing and rallies.  The BJ8 sports convertible was introduced in 1964 with a substantial power increase to 150 HP. Over 17,000 Mark III's were built with the majority coming to the US.  This particular car has gone through a restoration some time ago but still shows very well.  Furthermore this car starts perfectly and goes down the road strait and true.  There is plenty of power and this Healey gets a ton of looks.  Everything is in excellent working order as is the overdrive. The top and interior are equally as nice.  This would be an excellent candidate for tours or vintage rallies.
